LAGOS – Ohaji/Egbema youths on Wednesday embarked on a protest along the Owerri- Port Harcourt road, over the deplorable state of Avu – Obosima Umunwaku road, Ada-palm- Etekwuru road in Ohaji-Egbema Local Government Areas of Imo State. The youths blocked the highway for several hours protesting the deplorable condition of roads in the area, which left many commuters and motorists stranded for several hours. They displayed placards of various inscriptions which read ”SOS Avu – Obosima Umunwaku road, Ada-palm- Etekwuru road in Ohaji -Egbema Gov Hope Uzodinma, Attention: Avu – Obosima Umunwaku road, Ada-palm- Etekwuru road in Ohaji -Egbema has become dead zone and others, Speaking, spokesperson for the protesters, Emmanuel Ugorji, expressed disgust over the state of the roads and emphasized the need for the state government to fix them with a view to stopping incessant carnage therein. He said:“The suffering is so much that our people are very much aggrieved right now. The thought of another rainy season this year without any form of work on the Avu- Adapalm road is making them enraged in so much anger induced by their experiences on the road. “